On the first level, a hand-picked set of eight protein sequence database entries are listed, which correspond to inaccurate annotations, either as under-predictions (e.g.putative) or over-predictions (e.g. delta subunit). These specific entries have been verified in the course of our recent work [10], while other misassigned entries that are not detected by sequence similarity abound (e.g. CopG family transcriptional regulator from Sulfolobus islandicus with accession number YP_002828985.1, and 177 other entries – not shown) (Table 1).Table 1
